## Evidence

### SDK `createAgentSession` tool handling (source code)

**`dist/core/sdk.js`** — tool resolution logic:
```typescript
const defaultActiveToolNames = ["read", "bash", "edit", "write"];
const allowedToolNames = options.tools ?? (options.noTools === "all" ? [] : undefined);
const excludedToolNames = options.excludeTools;
const excludedToolNameSet = excludedToolNames ? new Set(excludedToolNames) : undefined;
const initialActiveToolNames = (options.tools ? [...options.tools] : options.noTools ? [] : defaultActiveToolNames)
  .filter((name) => !excludedToolNameSet?.has(name));
```

### `CreateAgentSessionOptions` interface (`dist/core/sdk.d.ts`):

```typescript
tools?: string[];           // Allowlist of tool names
excludeTools?: string[];    // Denylist, applied after tools allowlist
noTools?: "all" | "builtin"; // Bulk suppression modes
customTools?: ToolDefinition[]; // Additional tools to register
```

### `AgentSession._refreshToolRegistry()` (`dist/core/agent-session.js` line 1826):

Filters `_baseToolDefinitions` through `isAllowedTool(name)` which checks against `allowedToolNames` Set and `excludedToolNames`. Tools not in the allowed set are **never registered** in `_toolRegistry`, never wrapped, never appear in `agent.state.tools`.

### Extension runtime tool management (`dist/core/agent-session.js` line 1768):

```typescript
getActiveTools: () => this.getActiveToolNames(),
setActiveTools: (toolNames) => this.setActiveToolsByName(toolNames),
refreshTools: () => this._refreshToolRegistry(),
```

### `tool_call` blocking (`dist/core/extensions/runner.js` line 639):

```typescript
async emitToolCall(event) {
  for (const ext of this.extensions) {
    const handlers = ext.handlers.get("tool_call");
    for (const handler of handlers) {
      const handlerResult = await handler(event, ctx);
      if (handlerResult?.block) return handlerResult;
    }
  }
}
```

### CLI equivalents (`README.md`):

```bash
pi --tools read,grep,find,ls -p "Review the code"    # Allowlist
pi --exclude-tools bash                                 # Denylist
pi --no-tools                                           # All tools off
pi --no-builtin-tools                                   # Built-ins off, extensions on
```

---

## Caveats

- **`tools` allowlist is static at session creation.** Once `createAgentSession()` runs, the tool set is fixed. Use `setActiveTools()` for runtime changes.
- **`tool_call` block is a last-resort guard.** The tool still appears in the system prompt and the LLM may attempt to call it. Better to remove it from the active set entirely.
- **No `toolFilter` callback exists** in `createAgentSession` options. The filtering is purely list-based (`tools` allowlist + `excludeTools` denylist).
- **No `toolGuard` or `toolPolicy` pattern** exists in the SDK beyond the three mechanisms above.

